; Baseline: stack 128000, --heap 8M.
; History: the 64K (65000) AmigaOS default overflows on the GUI load path —
; nested bi_load frames + deep reader/compiler recursion while source-
; compiling gadtools.lisp / the Lambda's Tale amiga-ui.lisp macro tower.
; Before 2026-07-16 that overflow was SILENT corruption (the process wedged
; in the C runtime's exit path); the bisected workaround was stack 400000.
; The real fix (2026-07-16) shrank the per-recursion-level C frames
; (read_expr 5.1K->2K by hoisting the #* scan buffer; compile_and/or/cond/
; case/typecase 2-4KB->~0.2K via pending-jump chains threaded through the
; bytecode) and added a cl_check_c_stack call to read_expr — the reader,
; not cl_compile, was where the overflow actually happened, which is why
; the earlier compiler-only guard never fired.  VERIFIED on FS-UAE:
; full source compile of the game + amiga GUI libs passes at 128000; at
; 65000 the guard fires with a clean "C stack nearly exhausted in read"
; error and the session exits cleanly (no corruption, no hang).
; Single clamiga run (sequential allocations fragment Fast RAM on the
; lower-end target).  date timestamps before/after give total runtime;
; subtract the known ~38 s boot-to-REPL on this config to estimate
; test-suite time.
cd CLAmiga:
echo "=== avail before clamiga ===" >build/amiga/test-results.log
avail >>build/amiga/test-results.log
stack 128000
echo "=== run start ===" >>build/amiga/test-results.log
date >>build/amiga/test-results.log
build/amiga/clamiga --no-userinit --heap 8M --non-interactive --load tests/amiga/run-tests.lisp >>build/amiga/test-results.log
echo "=== run end ===" >>build/amiga/test-results.log
date >>build/amiga/test-results.log
; Quit FS-UAE so `make test-amiga` returns without manual intervention.
; The host-side watchdog (run-fs-uae.sh) is the fallback if this no-ops.
C:UAEquit
